    "body": "Issue Status: 1. Open 2. **Started** 3. Submitted 4. Done \n\n<hr>\n\n__Work has been started__.\n\n\nThese users each claimed they can complete the work by 266 years from now.\nPlease review their action plans below:\n\n\n**1) [zabalon26](https://gitcoin.co/zabalon26) has applied to start work _(Funders only: [approve worker](https://gitcoin.co/issue/eth-brownie/brownie/727/100024069?mutate_worker_action=approve&worker=zabalon26) | [reject worker](https://gitcoin.co/issue/eth-brownie/brownie/727/100024069?mutate_worker_action=reject&worker=zabalon26))_.**\n\nPlz choose me i have more than a few seemingly eternally pending transactions please\n**2) [hhio618](https://gitcoin.co/hhio618) has applied to start work _(Funders only: [approve worker](https://gitcoin.co/issue/eth-brownie/brownie/727/100024069?mutate_worker_action=approve&worker=hhio618) | [reject worker](https://gitcoin.co/issue/eth-brownie/brownie/727/100024069?mutate_worker_action=reject&worker=hhio618))_.**\n\nReally interested in doing this!\nMy plan:\n1. Estimate the gas price (I'll use pymaker solution here).\n2. Check for pending transactions within a fixed time (web3.eth.getBlock('pending')).\n3. Repricing and sending another transaction.\n4. Repeat until the transaction confirms (maybe add a repeat limit here!).\n**3) [iamdefinitelyahuman](https://gitcoin.co/iamdefinitelyahuman) has been approved to start work.**\n\nI have already completed the majority of work involved in this bounty.\n\nLearn more [on the Gitcoin Issue Details page](https://gitcoin.co/issue/eth-brownie/brownie/727/100024069).\n\n",
